<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/32804071-leeann"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/32804071-leeann">Leeann</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I chose to think it wasn't. I base that on the line about 4 years..... the doctor gave him related to his heart condition. I know that with the items <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I chose to think it wasn't. I base that on the line about 4 years..... the doctor gave him related to his heart condition. I know that with the items related to his after death desires sitting on the nightstand, it would make a reader think he planned his death. But, he had learned to love and live again.... so, it was just his time. I chose to believe he had those items on his bed stand every night because he knew he was on borrowed time. <br /><br />His heart was too big.... this also related to the level of caring he had for Sonja, rules, and the neighbor's kids.... It was a heart condition on several levels... <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
