<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/350109-how-do-you-pronounce-ove">How do you pronounce Ove?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_350109'><a id="like_count_community_question_350109" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/350109?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">125 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F20492604-a-man-called-ove">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/350109-how-do-you-pronounce-ove">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/350109-how-do-you-pronounce-ove">See all 37 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/34435488-erik-rosenberg"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/34435488-erik-rosenberg">Erik Rosenberg</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">See <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://forvo.com/word/ove/#sv'>http://forvo.com/word/ove/#sv</a> to hear it pronounced in Swedish. A somewhat close approximation in English is ooh-ve. ve as in &quot;vegetarian&quot; and ooh<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">See <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://forvo.com/word/ove/#sv">http://forvo.com/word/ove/#sv</a> to hear it pronounced in Swedish. A somewhat close approximation in English is ooh-ve. ve as in "vegetarian" and ooh like the standalone expression of dismay, not the oo sound of "glue"<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
